==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stripping
<hw>Strip"ping</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of one who strips.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mutual bows and courtesies . . . are remants of the original
prostrations and <qex>strippings</qex> of the captive.</q> <rj><qau>H.
Spencer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Never were cows that required such <qex>stripping</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Gaskell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>The last milk drawn from a cow at a
milking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strisores</ent>⟦br⟧
